              .col-lg-6
                .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body
                    h3.h5.card-title.text-primary
                      i.bi.bi-arrow-left-right.me-2
                      | Cross-Training
                    p.card-text
                      | Participate in cross-training within your team. By teaching your skills to others and learning from them, you ensure that multiple people are capable of handling various tasks, reducing dependency on any single individual.

              .col-12
                .card.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body
                    h3.h5.card-title.text-primary
                      i.bi.bi-gear.me-2
                      | Build Scalable and Maintainable Systems
                    p.card-text.mb-0
                      | Design your work, especially in software development, to be scalable and easily maintainable. Avoid overly complex solutions that only you can manage, and instead aim for clarity and simplicity.          // Knowledge Gatekeeping Section
          section#knowledge-gatekeeping.mb-5
            h2.h3.text-primary.mb-4
              i.bi.bi-shield-lock.me-2
              | Knowledge Gatekeeping
            p.lead.text-muted.mb-4 The Dangers of Hoarding Knowledge

            .row.mb-4
              .col-md-4.mb-3.mb-md-0
                figure.text-center
                  img.img-fluid.rounded.shadow-sm(
                    src='https://markhazleton.com/assets/img/MarkHazleton-Knowledge-Gatekeeping.png'
                    alt='Knowledge Gatekeeping'
                    title='Knowledge Gatekeeping. Image Credit: ChatGPT and Dall-E'
                    loading='lazy'
                  )
                  figcaption.text-muted.small.mt-2 Knowledge Gatekeeping Visualization
              .col-md-8
                p.lead
                  | There is a rational anxiety that comes from feeling that you can be replaced.
                  | This anxiety can manifest in behaviors aimed at projecting a sense of irreplaceability.
                p
                  | Developers may adopt tactics such as hoarding critical knowledge, creating dependencies on their unique skills,
                  | or establishing themselves as the sole experts in certain domains. While this knowledge gatekeeping might temporarily secure their position,
                  | they often have unintended negative consequences on team dynamics and the overall health of the organization.
                  | Understanding these behaviors is crucial in addressing the underlying fears
                  | and fostering a more collaborative and secure work environment.

            .alert.alert-warning.mb-4
              .d-flex.align-items-start
                i.bi.bi-exclamation-triangle-fill.text-warning.me-3.fs-4
                div
                  h4.alert-heading.h6.mb-2 Important Note
                  p.mb-0
                    | Knowledge gatekeeping is the opposite of developer obsolescence.
                    | Here are some key attributes of knowledge gatekeeping:

            .row.g-4.mb-4
              .col-lg-6
                .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body
                    h3.h5.card-title.text-danger
                      i.bi.bi-diagram-3.me-2
                      | Creation of Knowledge Silos
                    p.card-text
                      | Gatekeeping often results in the formation of knowledge silos,
                      | where critical information is confined to a single person or a small group.
                      | This isolation of knowledge hinders collaborative problem-solving and innovation,
                      | as it restricts the flow of ideas and information across the team.

              .col-lg-6
                .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body
                    h3.h5.card-title.text-danger
                      i.bi.bi-hourglass-split.me-2
                      | Dependency and Bottlenecks
                    p.card-text
                      | When certain individuals hoard knowledge,
                      | it creates a dependency on them for specific tasks or decisions.
                      | This not only places undue pressure on the gatekeepers
                      | but also creates bottlenecks in the workflow,
                      | slowing down timelines and reducing overall team efficiency.

              .col-lg-6
                .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body
                    h3.h5.card-title.text-danger
                      i.bi.bi-person-x.me-2
                      | Impaired Team Growth and Morale
                    p.card-text
                      | Knowledge gatekeeping can significantly stifle the professional growth of other team members.
                      | When information is not shared openly,
                      | it limits opportunities for learning and skill development for the rest of the team,
                      | potentially leading to lowered morale and job dissatisfaction.

              .col-lg-6
                .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body
                    h3.h5.card-title.text-danger
                      i.bi.bi-fire.me-2
                      | Increased Risk of Burnout
                    p.card-text
                      | Gatekeepers often face an overwhelming demand for their attention and expertise.
                      | This constant pressure can lead to burnout, affecting their productivity and well-being,
                      | and in turn, impacting the team's performance.

              .col-lg-6
                .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body
                    h3.h5.card-title.text-danger
                      i.bi.bi-lightbulb.me-2
                      | Innovation Stagnation
                    p.card-text
                      | In an environment where knowledge is closely guarded, there is a notable lack of diverse perspectives and ideas.
                      | This stagnation can prevent the development of innovative solutions,
                      | as fresh insights and creative problem-solving are constrained.

              .col-lg-6
                .card.h-100.border-0.shadow-sm
                  .card-body
                    h3.h5.card-title.text-danger
                      i.bi.bi-person-gear.me-2
                      | Challenges in Succession Planning
                    p.card-text
                      | Knowledge gatekeeping poses significant risks for succession planning.
                      | When critical knowledge is held by a few individuals,
                      | it becomes challenging to transfer skills and information when these individuals leave the organization or move to different roles.

            .alert.alert-success
